summary:
Proud and passionate sustainability ambassador, graduated jurist, active author/writer (printed/online articles). I love what I do and I work from my heart.

Founder and project leader of the civil community in Hungary "Do not feed the trash can" project, where thousands of people are rescuing eatable food on a daily basis and offering it to private people. Leading the community with passion and getting more and more media attention. Writing own articles about sustainability and participating in environmental friendly- related contests to able to spread the activity (currently active in seven towns with more than 8000 participants). Saved food per week average between 30-100 items/portions.

Goal of my life: proving that everyone can dream big and hard work/hard learning has result.

My work is characterized by accuracy and precision, I am not scared when I bump into a new situation, I
always consider it as a new challenge and try to do my best. Not afraid to ask for help, but if it is necessary, I am able to spend hours with figuring out the solution for myself - dependent on the situation. Moreover easy learner, highly- organized, hard-worker, detail oriented, keeping strictly the deadlines, teamplayer. 
Working for years in multicultural environment. Extreme SOP/notes maker (department SOP "author")- in order to work effectively.

Willingness to learn in my free time to improve the skills which are required by an job.
